# Test Plan â€“ E-commerce Web Application

## 1. Objective

The objective of this test plan is to validate the core functionality, usability, and reliability of the e-commerce web application.  
The focus is on identifying defects that may impact user experience, business flow integrity, and checkout completion.

---

## 2. Scope

### In Scope
- User Registration
- User Login / Logout
- Product Search & Filtering
- Product Details Page
- Add to Cart
- Update Cart
- Remove from Cart
- Checkout Process
- Form Validation

### Out of Scope
- Performance Testing
- Security Testing
- Payment Gateway Integration (real transactions)
- Mobile Application Testing

---

## 3. Test Strategy

Testing will include:

- Functional Testing of core business workflows
- Negative Testing for input validation
- Boundary Value Analysis
- Exploratory Testing focused on usability and session handling

---

## 4. Test Environment

- OS: Windows 10
- Browser: Google Chrome (latest version)
- Resolution: 1920x1080
- Test Data: Demo user accounts

---

## 5. Risk Analysis

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|------------|
| Checkout process failure | High | Full end-to-end test coverage |
| Invalid input handling | Medium | Negative & boundary testing |
| Session handling issues | Medium | Logout & session expiration tests |

---

## 6. Entry Criteria

- Application is deployed
- Environment accessible
- Test data available

---

## 7. Exit Criteria

- All high severity defects documented
- All planned test cases executed
- Test Summary Report completed

---

## 8. Deliverables

- Test Plan
- Test Cases
- Bug Reports
- Traceability Matrix
- Test Summary Report
